title: Corrections & Amplifications
text:
In some editions Wednesday, the first paragraph of a Business & Finance article about commuting to work incorrectly included the words "Compared with a year earlier," which weren't related to the article.

---

Kavitha Prasad, who oversees Intel Corp.'s artificial intelligence strategy, previously worked at a machine-learning startup where she was an early employee. An article about Intel in the April 11 Journal Report on Artificial Intelligence incorrectly said she co-founded the startup.

(See: "Artificial Intelligence (A Special Report) --- Inside Intel's AI-Chip Strategy: The company has lagged behind Nvidia in the fast-growing segment. It's determined to reverse that." -- WSJ Apr. 11, 2022)

---

Readers can alert The Wall Street Journal to any errors in news articles by e-mailing wsjcontact@wsj.com or by calling 888-410-2667.
